CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1956, pg. 14, reads: "Mary Dee...upsets disc jox"  Portion of accompanying article reads: "Charged air:  Little or no news seeped out of the disc jockeys' convention in Chicago, but in a closed session Pittsburgh's Mary Dee upset the air artists by demanding to know why a certain New York flak agent tried to "move in" on the public relations end.  Mary challenged the praise agent's presence in hall in the first place, and after a hot session, The P.A. saw his plan go awry as far as representing the disc jockeys is concerned..."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of WHOD radio disc jockey Mary Dee wearing halter top dress with square pendant necklace and teardrop earrings
